"```sql\nSELECT COUNT(*)\nFROM cards\nJOIN legalities ON cards.uuid = legalities.uuid\nJOIN rulings ON cards.uuid = rulings.uuid\nWHERE legalities.format = 'premodern'\n  AND rulings.text = 'This is a triggered mana ability.'\n  AND cards.side IS NULL;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of cards that meet the specified conditions: they are in the \"premodern\" format, have a ruling text of \"This is a triggered mana ability,\" and do not have multiple faces (indicated by `side IS NULL`). The query uses joins to connect the `cards`, `legalities`, and `rulings` tables based on the `uuid` foreign key relationships."